  "A boat travels 24 miles upstream in the same time it travels 36 miles downstream. If the river current is 3 mph, what is the boat's speed in still water?": "",
  "12 mph": "",
  "9 mph": "",
  "15 mph": "",
  "18 mph": "",
  "Set up 24/(b − 3) = 36/(b + 3). Cross-multiply: 24(b + 3) = 36(b − 3), giving 24b + 72 = 36b − 108, so 180 = 12b and b = 15 mph.": "",
  "A fill pipe can fill a tank in 6 hours and a drain can empty the tank in 8 hours. If both are open simultaneously, how long until the tank is full?": "",
  "7 hours": "",
  "24 hours": "",
  "14 hours": "",
  "48 hours": "",
  "Net rate: 1/6 − 1/8 = 4/24 − 3/24 = 1/24 of the tank per hour. Time to fill = 1 / (1/24) = 24 hours.": "",
